NEW YORK, April 13 (Xinhua) -- U.S.-listed Chinese companies traded higher on Wednesday with all the top 10 stocks by weight in the S&P U.S. Listed China 50 index ending the day on an upbeat note. Shares of XPeng and Pinduoduo jumped 7.29 percent and 5.88 percent, respectively,leading the gains in the top 10 stocks in the index. Shares of Bilibili and NIO climbed 5.21 percent and 4.93 percent, respectively, also among the best performers in the top 10 stocks. U.S. stocks advanced on Wednesday, buoyed by overall strength in tech names. The Dow Jones Industrial Average increased 344.23 points, or 1.01 percent, to 34,564.59. The S&P 500 rose 49.14 points, or 1.12 percent, to 4,446.59. The Nasdaq Composite Index was up 272.02 points, or 2.03 percent, to 13,643.59. The Cboe Volatility Index, widely considered as the best fear gauge in the stock market, dipped 10.06 percent to 21.82. As of Tuesday, the S&P U.S. Listed China 50 index, which is designed to track the performance of the 50 largest Chinese companies listed on U.S. exchanges by total market cap, stood at 2,300.45, marking a 2.04-percent slide for the month-to-date returns and a 22.76-percent loss for the year-to-date returns.  â– 